eals via tools like Finology Ticker. Don't panic; assess reasons, buyers, and remaining stakes before reacting.","summary":"Promoter stakes in Indian firms like IndiGo, Vedanta, and Whirlpool are falling, hitting an 8-year low by 2025. Reasons include debt repayment, high stock prices, SEBI's MPS rule, and personal diversification.\nInvestors should monitor promoter actions, FII/DII buying, and block deals via tools like Finology Ticker. Don't panic; assess reasons, buyers, and remaining stakes before reacting.","url":"https://www.livemint.com/market/stock-market-news/why-promoter-stakes-are-falling-in-indian-stocks-and-what-investors-should-track-11764750974830.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-03T16:41:58","source":"Livemint"},{"id":"393619","title":"Axis Capital downgrades Whirlpool India with a sell call, target price Rs 897, citing ownership clarity concerns.\nParent stake reduction may affect Whirlpool India's market share; it holds Rs 2,550 crore cash and RoCE of 38% in FY25.","summary":"Axis Capital downgrades Whirlpool India with a sell call, target price Rs 897, citing ownership clarity concerns.\nParent stake reduction may affect Whirlpool India's market share; it holds Rs 2,550 crore cash and RoCE of 38% in FY25.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/whirlpool-of-india-downgraded-to-sell-by-axis-capital-check-target-price-downside","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-11-28T13:43:14","source":"NDTV Profit"}]}]